I"?<p>The James-Lange theory of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/emotion-supports-memory-consolidation">emotion</a> argues that body states strongly modulate feelings. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/biofeedback-to-microexpressions-helps-regulate-affect">Ask someone to smile, and they will feel better</a>. Relax muscles with medication in anxiety patients and their <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cognitive-dissonance-reduction-drive-influences-body-state">body state</a> will induce a feeling of being at ease, which inhibits symptoms. In a sense, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mindfulness-breaks-self-induced-behaviors">behavior</a> is at the basis of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/premotor-theory-of-attention-is-fundamentally-enactive">high-level thought</a>.</p>
